# bin/.leakage-patterns -- LOCAL, GITIGNORED blocklist for validate-personas.sh
#
# One pattern per line (grep -iE extended-regex). Blank lines and lines starting
# with # are ignored. This file is the EXAMPLE -- copy to bin/.leakage-patterns
# and populate with the real identifiers for THIS environment. The real file is
# never committed; only this example template is tracked.
#
# Why local-only: the leak-detector itself must not publish the identifiers it
# is meant to catch. Hardcoding real names in a tracked script creates the
# exact leak it claims to prevent.
#
# Categories below are guidance; the script does not care about section headers.

# --- Target project slugs (one per real onboarded target) ---
# my-target-slug
# another-target
# acme-internal

# --- Target alternate spellings / display names ---
# MyTargetSlug
# my-target

# --- External system identifiers (DB project refs, account IDs, etc.) ---
# abcdefghijklmnopqrst       # supabase project ref shape, 20 lowercase chars

# --- Regulatory / industry-specific tokens used by target projects ---
# REGULATOR-ACRONYM
# DOMAIN-SPECIFIC-LAW
